Bring @water{2%cups} and @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} to a gentle simmer in a #small pot{} over low heat. Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1}. Pour @Whole Peeled Tomatoes{14%ounce} and their juices into a #medium bowl{}; using your hands, crush tomatoes into small pieces. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add garlic. Set aside 1 tsp shallot; add the rest to pan. Cook until fragrant, about ~{2%minutes}. Stir in @Arborio Rice{3/4%cup}, @Dried Oregano{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @Salt{}, and @Chili Flakes{1/4%tsp} (add up to 1/4 tsp more if you like spicy food). Stir until rice is translucent, about ~{30%seconds}.

Add stock, ½ cup at a time, to pan with rice, stirring after each addition. Allow rice to absorb most of stock before adding more. Repeat process until rice is just al dente, ~{20-25%minutes}. Add crushed tomatoes, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @Salt{1/2%tsp}. Increase heat to medium high and cook until creamy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Once risotto has simmered for ~{10%minutes}, heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add @Crab Cakes{10%ounce} and cook until browned and crispy, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

In a second medium bowl, whisk together the juice from 2 lemon wedges, a large drizzle of olive oil, reserved shallot, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and @Pepper{}. Toss in @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} until thoroughly coated.

Place @Butter{2%TBSP} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave on high until just softened, about ~{10%seconds} (if melted, start over). Stir in half the lemon zest, a pinch of remaining chili flakes, and salt.

Stir @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} and @Butter{1%TBSP} into pan with risotto; season with salt and pepper. Divide between bowls. Top with crab cakes and lemon chili butter. Sprinkle with remaining lemon zest if desired. Serve with salad and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Feeling devilish? You'll love this take on fra diavolo with risotto and crab cakes topped with lemon chili butter.